{
  "texts": [
    "Intuitively, the numerator describes",
    "the size of the point-at-target component of the decoder output, and the denominator describes the size of the trial-to-trial variability.",
    "To simulate neural activity, we used the laterality encoding model in Eq.",
    "(4) where we varied the directional tuning correlation between the hands and the size of the laterality dimension (as labeled along the x-and y-axes of Fig. 3d, e).",
    "We began by generating a synthetic target dataset containing unimanual velocities for the left and right hands."
  ]
}